title: Independent candidate Abdul Kareem wins PK-51 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Abdul Kareem has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-51 Swabi-III by securing 39,653 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz’s Nawabzada who bagged 17,898 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 41.26 per cent.
